Edit make_gofnt.pro with the desired emission lines and location of CHIANTI files. CHIANTI can be used to identify these.

Run this with:

idl -e "make_goft"

Run the line synthesis using:

python synthesise_spectra.py

This can require lots of memory at full resolution, so a fully synthesised atmosphere using the Cheung+2018 atmosphere (doi:10.1038/s41550-018-0629-3) of the Fe XII 195.119 and 195.179 with 5 background lines from each side included, can be downloaded here:

https://liveuclac-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/ucasjem_ucl_ac_uk/Es-ts6rwXIlInAweGI7hmdMB5BoGqv9uSpIXOvMkzhS3cw?e=54si7R

Run the instrument response function using:

python instr_response.py --config ./run/input/config.yaml

This can be looped in bash using:

for config in ./run/input/*.yaml; do
  python instr_response.py --config "$config"
done